==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: egg and dart
<hw>egg and dart</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos>
<def>a decorative ovolo molding, having a series of egg-shaped figures
alternating with another shape in the form of a dart or anchor. Also
used attributively; <as>as, an <ex>egg-and-dart</ex> molding; an
<ex>egg-and-dart</ex> design</as>. Called also <altname>egg and
dart</altname>, and <altname>egg and tongue</altname></def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> egg-and-anchor, egg and anchor, egg-and-tongue, egg
and tongue.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>egg-and-tongue</ent>⟦br⟧
